00:59:15,835 --> 00:59:17,135
("Fate", First draft)

783
00:59:17,135 --> 00:59:19,195
The person whom I trusted the most...

784
00:59:20,965 --> 00:59:23,095
The man whom I thought of like my own father...

785
00:59:25,695 --> 00:59:27,265
stabbed me in the back.

786
00:59:44,935 --> 00:59:47,235
Are you not even going to offer me a cup of tea?

787
01:00:01,535 --> 01:00:02,995
("Fate", First draft)

788
01:00:40,265 --> 01:00:41,265
("Fate", First draft)

789
01:01:28,465 --> 01:01:29,835
What are you doing there?

790
01:01:38,063 --> 01:01:41,093
You know how every writer feels about his writing room.

791
01:01:42,433 --> 01:01:44,333
How can you just walk in here without my permission?

792
01:01:44,763 --> 01:01:48,033
I see that you have something writers should not have.

793
01:01:51,633 --> 01:01:54,733
Wouldn't it be wise to get rid of things that could become problems?

794
01:01:57,893 --> 01:02:00,833
I'm just going to think that I didn't see it. Put this away.

795
01:02:04,463 --> 01:02:07,963
I came to see you as I was worried you might be upset over the article.

796
01:02:08,263 --> 01:02:12,233
But it looks like visiting you was a mistake.

797
01:02:54,033 --> 01:02:55,363
What do you want from me?

798
01:02:55,763 --> 01:02:57,963
Why did you show up in my life like this?

799
01:02:59,193 --> 01:03:01,133
Please calm down, Mr. Han.

800
01:03:01,493 --> 01:03:04,733
Are you doing this to ruin my life? Is that it?

801
01:03:05,393 --> 01:03:07,933
If that's what you're thinking, don't even dream. It won't happen.

802
01:03:09,333 --> 01:03:12,033
I won't be broken easily.

803
01:03:13,693 --> 01:03:16,263
Do you even know what I've been through to get here?

804
01:03:16,763 --> 01:03:18,863
I will not fall because of a punk like you!

805
01:03:33,493 --> 01:03:35,163
By any chance,

806
01:03:37,633 --> 01:03:39,333
did you use to be a ghost writer yourself too?

807
01:03:42,633 --> 01:03:45,233
Did you write Baek Tae Min's "Fate" for him?

808
01:03:47,563 --> 01:03:49,493
Were you his ghost writer?

809
01:04:00,193 --> 01:04:01,293
Get out.

810
01:04:14,233 --> 01:04:15,263
I...

811
01:04:16,763 --> 01:04:19,363
I'd much rather let someone steal my writing...

812
01:04:20,633 --> 01:04:22,333
than taking credit for someone else's work.

813
01:04:42,163 --> 01:04:43,533
("Chicago Typewriter")

814
01:04:49,633 --> 01:04:51,563
("Chicago Typewriter")

815
01:05:57,933 --> 01:06:00,663
(Chicago Typewriter)

816
01:06:01,033 --> 01:06:04,093
I must've been the biggest traitor to my country in my past life.

817
01:06:04,093 --> 01:06:07,333
The person whom I never wanted to forget about even after death...

818
01:06:07,463 --> 01:06:09,433
Seol! Did you want to do things like this?

819
01:06:09,433 --> 01:06:12,433
You have no clue. Every fan would die for this.

820
01:06:12,433 --> 01:06:14,733
"Did you see? He and I are this close."

821
01:06:14,733 --> 01:06:16,233
- I'm sorry. - "I love you"?

822
01:06:16,233 --> 01:06:17,863
The next episode hasn't been published yet.

823
01:06:17,863 --> 01:06:19,633
Was my manuscript not helpful?

824
01:06:19,633 --> 01:06:22,563
I decided to come here to put an end to the rumor that I have...

825
01:06:22,563 --> 01:06:23,693
a ghost writer.

826
01:06:23,668 --> 01:06:25,038
Thank you for everything.

827
01:06:25,063 --> 01:06:26,533
I don't need you anymore.

828
01:06:26,533 --> 01:06:27,863
Keep writing.

829
01:06:27,863 --> 01:06:29,633
Only then, I'll live.
